# CSS Pseudo Elements

Pseudo elements style specific parts of an element.

## Common Pseudo Elements

### ::before

Adds content before an element.

```css
h1::before {
    content: "🚀 ";
}
```

### ::after

Adds content after an element.

```css
h1::after {
    content: " 🔥";
}
```

### ::first-letter

Styles the first letter.

```css
p::first-letter {
    font-size: 40px;
    font-weight: bold;
}
```

### ::first-line

Styles the first line.

```css
p::first-line {
    color: blue;
}
```

### ::selection

Styles highlighted text.

```css
::selection {
    background: yellow;
}
```

## Real World Example

News websites use first-letter styling to create attractive article layouts.

## Benefits

- Cleaner HTML
- Better styling flexibility
- Improved visual presentation

## Summary

Pseudo elements enhance design without adding extra HTML elements.
